1: The US Stablecoin Bill will be advanced in the House Committee on April 2;
2: Bitcoin spot ETF had a total net inflow of 83.0919 million US dollars yesterday, and Ethereum spot ETF had a total net outflow of 18.6309 million US dollars yesterday;
3: Fidelity will launch a tokenized fund that invests in US Treasury bonds to compete with BlackRock's BUIDL;
4: Whales unlocked 38,821 SOLs after a year of silence, but still faced a loss of more than 100,000 US dollars;
5: The LAYER giant whale that opened a position three weeks ago is suspected of clearing its position to stop profit, or making a profit of 1.704 million US dollars;
6: Amber Group recharged 10.35 million US dollars of ENA to Binance in the past 12 hours;
7: Movement Network announced the postponement of MoveDrop to optimize ecological integration and security audits;
8: Nick Tomaino: Ethereum has become the dominant ecosystem for the tokenization of real assets.
